  "prompt": "Why do American writers use yellow paper?",
  "response": "American writers might use yellow paper for several reasons, although it's less about American writers alone and more about general use:\n\n1. **Eye Comfort:** Yellow paper can be easier on the eyes compared to white paper. It reduces glare and eye strain, especially under bright lights.\n\n2. **Creativity and Focus:** Some people believe that the color yellow stimulates creativity and mental focus. Writers might choose yellow paper to create a more conducive environment for creative work.\n\n3. **Contrast and Readability:** Notes and texts written on yellow paper can have better contrast and readability, making it easier to review and organize ideas.\n\n4. **Tradition and Preference:** Over time, yellow paper, such as legal pads, has become a traditional choice for writers, academics, and professionals. This preference might be purely habitual.\n\n5. **Organization:** Using different colored papers can help writers organize their notes and drafts more effectively.\n\nHowever, it\u2019s important to note that not all American writers use yellow paper, and paper color choice can be highly individual and based on personal preference.",
